Coloration. In 70 % ethanol: Dorsum and upper flanks reddish beige to light gray. Lower flanks beige, trending lighter toward cream-colored belly. Nasal and maxillary barbels with gray basally, becoming lighter distally. Mandibular barbels cream colored. Dorsum coloration extending onto base of dorsal and adipose fins; both fins with lighter outer margin, very thin on adipose fin. Pectoral, pelvic, and anal fins with very faint pigmented area at base, otherwise uniformly cream colored. Caudal fin uniformly dusky, upper rays slightly more so than lower. Live color similar, but with a strong brownish- or orange-yellow hue (
Fig. 2
).
